                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4698: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-24T10:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 24, 1931—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 24—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>264. From Gibson. After the end of the Conference of Ministers yesterday, the
                    Committee of Experts resumed its meetings.</p>
                <p>As can best be seen now several days will be taken up in collating the basic
                    facts. General Dawes will be back in London by the time that work is completed.
                    Technical experts who rely upon their Ambassadors for political guidance are
                    representing the other Governments. As soon as General Dawes is settled here it
                    seems to me that <pb facs="0283" n="169" xml:id="pg_169"/> the normal course
                    would be to have Livesey depend upon him for guidance and to have me return to
                    Brussels. Of course I would not leave before the General could take over
                    conveniently.</p>
                <p>Secretary Stimson, with whom I have discussed the foregoing, authorizes me to
                    state that he concurs. Gibson.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
